      <trans-unit id="14653" identifier="c4273cfcf0d560b5128dcd4e284b53de">
        <source>Description of different angles:</source>
        <target>crwdns14653:0crwdne14653:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14654" identifier="8db6461be20765ba424e082d5fa580fe">
        <source>An acute angle is an angle between 0 and 90 degrees (not including 90).</source>
        <target>crwdns14654:0crwdne14654:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14655" identifier="01a503f2a30e3c0239055a94b4b5a907">
        <source>A right angle is a 90 degrees angle.</source>
        <target>crwdns14655:0crwdne14655:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14656" identifier="53a8d8f22c1a483badf1647dc341de9b">
        <source>Obtuse angle is an angle between 90 and 180 degree (not including 90 and 180).</source>
        <target>crwdns14656:0crwdne14656:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14657" identifier="4ddb0c9081547d67ed0f8ef83417e337">
        <source>A straight angle is a 180 degrees angle.</source>
        <target>crwdns14657:0crwdne14657:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14658" identifier="09fd8a641ba968dfe5b4b7e3f0a027f7">
        <source>A reflex angle is an angle greater than 180 degrees.</source>
        <target>crwdns14658:0crwdne14658:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[5]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14659" identifier="3b466192f6533f1f4909b1189b4e4bfe">
        <source>There are different ways to program checking the range using the &lt;strong&gt;if()/else&lt;/strong&gt; blocks.
Below are hints for two different ways you may program this:</source>
        <target>crwdns14659:0crwdne14659:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14660" identifier="17a325b3062a62a48706f67f7f5a2261">
        <source>Use a series of &lt;strong&gt;if()&lt;/strong&gt; blocks sequentially checking for the ranges in each if() block.</source>
        <target>crwdns14660:0crwdne14660:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul[2]/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14661" identifier="77e428b380f641c03b093bc6eb24792f">
        <source>If you need to check a range between two values you can use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:&amp;lt;&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; operator in the condition for your if() block (the AND operator reports true if both conditions are true).</source>
        <target>crwdns14661:0crwdne14661:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul[2]/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14662" identifier="632caaf00b97d459c12e7ae91a75e5a9">
        <source>Use nested &lt;strong&gt;if()&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;if()/else&lt;/strong&gt; blocks, which are &lt;strong&gt;if()/else&lt;/strong&gt; blocks inside another set of &lt;strong&gt;if()/else&lt;/strong&gt; blocks (i.e. a nested conditional statement is a conditional statement where the &lt;strong&gt;if()&lt;/strong&gt; and/or &lt;strong&gt;else&lt;/strong&gt; contains another conditional statement).</source>
        <target>crwdns14662:0crwdne14662:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul[2]/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14663" identifier="3f34fd497a496467d16d0e9677596e65">
        <source>For example:</source>
        <target>crwdns14663:0crwdne14663:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul[2]/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14664" identifier="08bdf0089b6ee7c3822f63e868d98478">
        <source>if &amp;lt;[angle] &amp;lt; [180]&amp;gt; then
  if &amp;lt;[angle] &amp;lt; [90]&amp;gt; then
    acute angle :: custom
  else
    if &amp;lt;[angle] = [90]&amp;gt; then
      right angle :: custom
    else
      obtuse angle :: custom
    end
  end
else
  if &amp;lt;[angle] = [180]&amp;gt; then
    straight angle :: custom
  else
    reflex angle :: custom
  end
end</source>
